title: FibriCheck - Check your heart, prevent strokes
description:
Check your heart rhythm with the medically certified FibriCheck app on your smartphone. Keep an eye on the health of your heart, detect cardiac arrhythmias in good time, and avoid complications such as a stroke. Have you been diagnosed with cardiac arrhythmia in the past? You can also use the app to monitor your arrhythmia.


Measure your heart rhythm with your smartphone


• Quick and easy: It takes just 60 seconds to check your heart rhythm. Place your finger on the camera of your smartphone, and put your mind at ease.

• No need for another device: All you need to take measurements is your smartphone.

• Measure whenever you want: Are you experiencing symptoms, such as palpitations? Open the app and take a measurement immediately.

• Regular measurements: With FibriCheck, you can measure your heart rhythm twice daily. This way any changes in your heart rhythm will be detected more quickly.

• Notifications: Set up notifications for your measurements.


Request a review of your measurements


• Reports:  After your measurement, we will send you a detailed report with clear advice.

• Share your results with your doctor:  You can easily share the medical report with your family doctor or cardiologist. Please note: in Australia and America, FibriCheck can only be used under the supervision of a licensed healthcare practitioner.

• Medical experts:  Has our app detected an irregular measurement? Ask our team of medical experts to review your results.


Medically developed and approved


• Developed on the basis of PPG: PPG is a technique with ECG quality that uses light to detect cardiac arrhythmias. It measures changes in the size of your blood vessels by using the flash of your smartphone camera. These are then converted into heart rhythm measurements.

• Developed together with doctors: FibriCheck was developed in collaboration with a reputable Belgian hospital and university.

• Medically approved: FibriCheck is trusted by doctors and researchers worldwide thanks to its CE marking and FDA and TGA approvals. Please note: in Australia and America, FibriCheck can only be used under the supervision of a licensed healthcare practitioner.

• Approved by ORCHA: ORCHA, the world's leading health app evaluation & advisor organisation, gave us a quality score of 85%.


Try FibriCheck free of charge for 24 hours. After that, you can keep an eye on your heart’s health starting from € 3,99 per month.
 (Note that exact prices can vary depending on your location, currency and exchange rates.)

The FibriCheck application has FDA and TGA approvals and is a fully-fledged Class IIa medical device under the Medical Devices Directive (93/42/EEC).
Its manufacturer, Qompium nv, is ISO 13485:2016 certified.


The instructions for use are available in the app and on our website: https://pages.fibricheck.com/ifu/app

title: 2 Stroke Porting
description:
Have you tuned a two stroke and wondered when your exhaust and transfer ports need to open in order to get maximum power at the rpm you want? 2 Stroke Porting will tell you. Simply move the slider to the rpm where you want the maximum power to be and it will display the required exhaust and transfer openings.

 

The openings will be displayed in - degrees After Top Dead Centre (ATDC), degrees duration and, for those who prefer distance measurements - Distances in millimetres from piston at Top Dead Centre to port opening (for distance measurements, make sure you insert your Stroke and Connector Rod lengths). You can also measure from the top of the cylinder surface, but if your piston doesn’t reach the top at TDC, you’ll need to add this to the measurement displayed in the app

 

2 Stroke Porting is also good for assessing what state of tune you already have. Either measure the port distances from TDC, or measure opening time, ATDC, with a degree wheel, slide the slider so the it shows the port opening at this measurement and read off the rpm where the maximum power should be.

 

2 Stroke Porting will also highlight to you whether your existing exhaust and transfer timings are in tune with each other. On some older two strokes the relationship between the exhaust and transfers was inadequate. Slide the slider to the degrees, or distance measurement, where your exhaust port opens, then you will have a degree and millimetre measurement of where your transfers should open and you can check your engine to see if they do.

 

2 stroke Porting is a really good guide to establish these measurements and will give you very close figures to work from. To maximise your output ensure you have a good exhaust, correct size carb and a cylinder head with well designed squish area.

title: Stroke App:Spoke
description: Stroke App:Spoke is a mobile application which initiates emergency call with a single click and enables providers to assess and monitor stroke patients. The solution includes internet audio and video call, secure text and customizable rules with capability to broadcast messages and group calls. Doctor will receive call on TiaTele Doctor mobile application based on on-call schedule. Physician scheduler is integrated for the 1st on call and 2nd on call doctors Vascular and Interventional Neurology doctors. Hardware devices includes Telemedicine cart with IP camera, iMac and various wrireless medical equipments. The stroke workflow guides the physicians through NIH Stroke Scale assessment and stroke protocol chart as guidelines for diagnosing and making treatment decisions. Patient status with time tracking from ‘Last Known Well’ and ‘Door-​to-​Needle Time’ is shown for analyzing the stroke protocol execution efficiency.

title: Aphasia Speech Therapy
description:
This App helps to improve the Speech capabilities of an Aphasia patient..

This App helps to improvise from the inability but can not cure any disease. This is only an alternative method to practice. Please consider your speech therapist thoughts before installing this app. 

Developer is not responsible for any side effects.

This App has all the required basic auditory and Vocal related pictures, voice assistant and one can enter the script and the assistant will help in repeating the same. New features like testing and memory methods will help in remembering.

This App was tested 100% on Aphasia patients and have seen a gradual improvement in the speech and language of them. 

As per the recommendation from the various speech pathologists, we are actually releasing this app to the public.

We are getting feedback and we are actually implementing the changes one after one, so the version of the app increases more number of features we are actually adding.

This App has dark colors, we intentionally kept dark colors as to grab more concentration of Aphasia patients. Too much of white background will kill the interest, so we didn't prefer much white back ground.

This App contains Ads, Ad revenue is used to develop more useful apps to the society.

This App has been developed based on taking the views of many Speech Therapist all over India, Thanks to one and all for helping us.

title: Stoke Patient
description:
Stroke Patient is designed specifically for patients recovering from a stroke, their families and their friends. It helps to explain strokes, available treatments and the hospital care process. 

The app, created by a team of stroke specialists, provides easy-to-understand information on strokes and emergency stroke treatments. 

Key Features: 

- 5 Stage Hospital Treatment Diagram 

- Simple information on stroke, its causes, prevention tips and recovery process 

- Glossary - medical terms explained

description:
PLAY SMARTER GOLF
TaylorMade’s myRoundPro provides an unprecedented statistical analysis experience, designed to help every golfer better understand, adapt, and improve their game.
 
With the myRoundPro app, you can track your rounds on the go, enabling you to record your scores, check detailed yardages with built-in GPS, analyze every shot on a map of the course, and begin to identify areas for improvement.

Based on the record of your shots and scores, myRoundPro analyzes golfers’ statistics to include new data such as Strokes Gained, proximity to the hole, and classic statistics like fairways hit and greens in regulation—giving the golfer all the data they need to adapt and help improve the way they play.

comments: Just finished first round. No complaints. Works perfectly on Galaxy gear as well. Edit I've noticed that the meterage seems to be out by about +8% while playing. I have everything switched from yards to meters but still get about 217m on the 200m marker at multiple courses. Same with stroke distances. 275m drive on the watch is down to 255m when reviewing the round on the phone after. Using galaxy watch and pixel 3 phone in australia.

Loved this app up until yesterday. It was the only reason I bought a Samsung Active2 watch. Worked fantastic until Samsung released the latest OS for the Active2. This app no longer works. It loads on the watch but when you click "Add New Round" on the watch nothing happens. Was able to replicate the issue on another Active2. I despise sloppy testing. New releases should not break functionality on apps. The app runs fine on the phone but super clunky to use that interface while golfing.

Great; when it works. Positive: Runs on Samsung watch, so there's no need to be pulling out your phone after every stroke. Shows distance to hole at a glance. A single tap records each stroke with club, position, and distance. Stats and analysis of individual rounds and aggregate. Negative: Occasionally does not upload results at end of round, which are then lost. No support (none!), limited documentation. Distances are generally spot-on but occasionally wildly inaccurate (with no in-between). Although rounds are uploaded (usually) to cloud there is no way to view anything on the web; you must use your phone/tablet. Recommended for casual golfer.

I'm going to echo what others are saying. Loved this app up until 9/25/2020. It was the only reason I bought a Samsung Active2 watch. Worked fantastic until Samsung released the latest OS for the Active2. This app no longer works. It loads on the watch but when you click "Add New Round" on the watch nothing happens. Please fix. Prior to this issue I'd give it a solid 5 stars for its watch capabilities. Now 0. Please fix this error.

Needs a Quick scoring option in addition to individual club tracking. If you End Round with no club selection (score is zero), golfer should be able to add score with + and - buttons and confirm. Love app otherwise. Many times golfers don't want to be forced into detailed scoring. Works great on my Active 2.

title: Atrial Fibrillation Risk - Stroke, TIA, Embolism
description:
"Atrial Fibrillation Risk - Stroke, TIA, Embolism" is a mobile app designed to help medical practitioner to predict the risk of stroke, transient ischemic attack (TIA), or embolism based on CHA₂DS₂-VASc Score. Atrial fibrillation (AF) is the most common sustained cardiac rhythm disorder, which is associated with a substantial risk of mortality and morbidity from stroke and thromboembolism (TE) event.

There are several features of "Atrial Fibrillation Risk - Stroke, TIA, Embolism", namely:
🔸 Simple and very easy to use.
🔸 Precise calculation with CHA₂DS₂-VASc Score.
🔸 Determine the risk of atrial fibrillation complication, such as stroke, transient ischemic attack, and embolism.
🔸 It is totally free. Download now!

The CHA2DS2-VASc score in "Atrial Fibrillation Risk - Stroke, TIA, Embolism" are clinical prediction rules for estimating the risk of stroke in patients with non-rheumatic atrial fibrillation (AF), a common and serious heart arrhythmia associated with thromboembolic stroke. Such a score is used to determine whether or not treatment is required with anticoagulant or antiplatelet therapy. This schema could improve the approach to stroke risk stratification in patients with atrial fibrillation (AF) by using "Atrial Fibrillation Risk - Stroke, TIA, Embolism" app.

Disclaimer: all calculations must be re-checked and should not be used alone to guide patient care, nor should they substitute for clinical judgment. Calculations in this "Atrial Fibrillation Risk - Stroke, TIA, Embolism" app might be different with your local practice. Consult to expert doctor whenever necessary.

title: World Stroke Academy
description:
The World Stroke Academy app is the official mobile learning app of the World Stroke Organization (WSO).

This app offers access to hundreds of educational materials and activities published by the WSO and in collaboration with various global partners in medical health, with a focus on frontline clinical stroke care.

For our membership and stroke community we release eLearning programs on an annual basis and provide access to accredited courses (EACCME,...), educational webcasts, PPT shared, learning modules, webinars, e-posters, abstracts, journal articles and more, that we invite you to discover on this app. The World Stroke Academy app’s discussion forums allow you to interact with your peers at any time, while completing learning modules, or viewing lectures, and features a powerful search system allowing end-users to easily find precise materials and activities, and even matching slides.

Premium access is free for WSO members, others may purchase a digital premium access through the app.

Should you require technical support, please contact the World Stroke Academy support team at support@world-stroke-academy.org

Requires a WSO Membership or a World Stroke Academy Account and an Internet connection, designed for compatible Android devices and versions.

2018© World Stroke Organization.

Published under license from MULTILEARNING Group Inc.; World Stroke Organization's digital education content provider.

title: Stroke pocketcards
description:
The Stroke pocketcards contain a collection of valuable clinical information on the diagnosis and management of stroke, including:

- An algorithm for the emergency management of acute stroke
- tPA administration guidelines, including complete tPA inclusion and exclusion criteria and guidelines for management of patients receiving tPA
- Indications and guidelines for intra-arterial thrombolysis and mechanical clot extraction
- Quick reference tables for localization of TIAs and strokes, including descriptions of anterior and posterior circulation syndromes
- Illustrations of cerebral and brain stem vasculature and vascular territories
- The NIH Stroke Scale and information on the clinical prognosis of stroke
- Descriptions and indications for use of imaging modalities in stroke management
- Recommendations for stroke workup, hospital management and supportive care
- Secondary stroke prevention recommendations, including guidelines for carotid endarterectomy and antithrombotic therapy in atrial fibrillation


Features
► Easy navigation to critical information.
► Multiple navigation possibilities via TOC view and Classic View
► Well illustrated charts,tables and diagrams.
► Zoomable "Classic View" for rapid access
► BBiTools section to keep you updated with our latest apps in the appstore
► Free Updates
► Email support

title: Orientate
description:
Orientate”, is a Laterality Recognition Program that forms part of a Graded Motor Imagery, a rehabilitation program based on clinical trials to treat pain and movement problems.

Laterality recognition or Left / Right Discrimination are known to occur in stroke patients and patients with CRPS/RSD and phantom limb pain. The ability to identify Left or Right is important for normal recovery. Orientate” laterality software provide images of hands and feet in different positions and postures, on nine levels, totalling over one thousand five hundred images.

Research shows the ability to identify Left and Right is slower and less accurate in people suffering from pain, and there is a direct link to the ability to correctly recognize Left and Right to the level of pain. Orientate” has been developed to measure this ability, and help retrain the brain. 

Stroke patients may lose the ability to recognize a complete left or right hemisphere. As part of a comprehensive rehabilitation program Orientate” will help to retrain the brain to see and recognize this missing hemisphere and aid the remapping of the brain. 

Like all therapies laterality recognition dose not always show immediate results. The rate and amount of recovery much depends on the extent of the damage, and the intensity and duration of the therapy you receive. Recovery also is likely to be influenced by personality, life experiences and coping styles. Motivation to recover is a key factor in obtaining an optimal level of rehabilitation.

Learn more about graded motor imagery rehabilitation at http://www.mirrorboxtherapy.com 

Try for yourself the first three levels completely free.

As I previously stated I'm a first time user, & was reading everything I can before the app. It was reccommended by PT for my CRPS in my knee, which this app doesn't address but the concept is still helpful. On your about page you have words like yarning instead of yawning, that needs to be change. There are a few more edits needed, but that jumped off the page.

Fantastic tool. Worth it for medical professionals and their patients/clients right across the entire pain spectrum to start the "self" rediscovery journey to self management with little to no medical intervention. What a gift for all of us who suffer 24/7 with these horrible & debilitating "invisible" (& therefore usually dismissed, belittled & not often believed) chronic/complex nerve pain syndromes. Maybe this could even help save some lives. Going to share the hell out of this app to get the word put. Well done Development Team! .. Thankyou

not as easy as you would think it would be! Really makes you think! I can see why this may help with my condition of CRPS! My Dr. wants me to use the program three times a day for three times a day for the first month, and then once a day there after. Thanks for giving the first levels for free! I have been using for a full month now snd plan to keep using the program!
This is a very good app to retrain the brain and it's fun at the same time.

title: Aphasia Speech Therapy
description:
Aphasia is an impairment of language, affecting the production or comprehension of speech and the ability to read or write. Aphasia is always due to injury to the brain-most commonly from a stroke, particularly in older individuals. But brain injuries resulting in aphasia may also arise from head trauma, from brain tumors, or from infections.

Aphasia can be so severe as to make communication with the patient almost impossible, or it can be very mild. It may affect mainly a single aspect of language use, such as the ability to retrieve the names of objects, or the ability to put words together into sentences, or the ability to read. More commonly, however, multiple aspects of communication are impaired, while some channels remain accessible for a limited exchange of information.

It is the job of the professional to determine the amount of function available in each of the channels for the comprehension of language, and to assess the possibility that treatment might enhance the use of the channels that are available.

In this App you can find more information on the different types of aphasia such as Global, Broca’s, Wernicke’s, Primary Progressive, Anomic, and Mixed Non-fluent aphasia.

title: Health4TheWorld
description:
The HEALTH4THEWORLD STROKE HOPE APP is a free of cost educational tool to spread knowledge about stroke risk factors, secondary prevention, post stroke mobility & exercise education and speech strategies.  It has been created by Health4TheWorld which is a non profit organization inspired by the unmet medical needs worldwide. The mission of the organization is solving health inequities through innovation & technology and bringing smiles around the world. Please learn more about us at www.health4theworld.org.

With an estimated incidence of 16.9 million and a prevalence of 33 million according to the World Health Organization, stroke is a dominant diseased entity in the category of cardiovascular diseases, and is a leading cause of serious long-term disability. The global burden of stroke falls disproportionately on low and middle-income countries, prompting us to improve global health educational outreach. We hope that this stroke educational app will be helpful.

title: Stroke TeleCare
description:
Stroke or Brain attack is a preventable leading cause of sudden death and it is one most common cause of chronic disability. There is FDA approved highly indicated medicine (thrombolytic agents) available for treatment of stroke. But unfortunately only upto 4 to 5% of stroke patients manage to receive this wonderful medicine. One of the major hurdles being they (patients) don’t reach Hospital/Stroke centre within the golden period (window period) of symptom onset, which tragically increased mortality and morbidity. 

Stroke is Preventable, Treatable and even Curable.... But we need a comprehensive team effort..     

Keeping this in mind, distinguished stroke experts across India and abroad in collaboration with leading hospitals from India, Singapore,USA, Canada and others formed a comprehensive “Stroke Telecare” support group. The mobile “Stroke TeleCare” application compatible with mobile platform Android™ (Google, Mountain View, CA) and iOS (Apple, Cupertino, CA) will be immensely helpful in guiding management of acute stroke at a remote trained and certified stroke centre. 

The App has been designed with enhanced microprocessor capacities making it possible for easy and fast image and video processing including linked videoconference.

title: Constant Therapy
description:
Constant Therapy is an award-winning speech therapy app designed to help people cope with aphasia, dementia and other speech, language and cognitive disorders caused by stroke or traumatic brain injuries. To date, thousands of users have completed over 110 million exercises using Constant Therapy. 

BENEFITS

•        Practice speech, language, cognition, memory, reading, attention and comprehension skills anytime, anywhere
•        Choose your recovery goals and we’ll deliver personalized tasks to help you get there
•        See your progress in real time on your performance dashboard
•        Access a library of evidence-based exercises developed by neuroscientists and clinicians 
•        Get the most out of Constant Therapy with one-on-one help from Customer Support specialists 
•        Try before you subscribe with a 2-week free trial
•        Pair the app with cognitive and speech therapy you’re already doing in the clinic (even add your clinician so they can monitor your progress)


The Science Behind Constant Therapy:

Constant Therapy was designed by scientists at Boston University, and has won awards from the American Stroke Association and AARP. The clinically-proven app is recommended by speech language pathologists, neurologists and occupational therapists.

In a recent study of post-stroke rehabilitation practices published in Frontiers in Neurology, outcomes were compared among 3,686 patients who used tablet-based therapy at home independently and those who completed the same therapy in a clinic under the guidance of a clinician. The study found tablet-based home users mastered skills in a shorter time and practiced therapy more frequently than clinic users. Nearly one third (29%) of users who made gains were 71 years old or more, and the oldest user was 97 years old.*

Using Constant Therapy

- Try before you subscribe with a free 14-day trial

- Users can choose from two subscription plans: $24.99 per month or $249.99 per year.

Contact Us

Email – support@constanttherapy.com

Visit Online – https://thelearningcorp.com/constant-therapy/

Privacy Policy – https://thelearningcorp.com/privacy/

Terms of Use – https://thelearningcorp.com/eula/


* Study published in Frontiers in Neurology, “Comparison of Therapy Practice at Home and in the Clinic: A Retrospective Analysis of the Constant Therapy Platform Data Set,” may be found at: https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fneur.2019.00140/full

** Constant Therapy does not provide rehabilitation services and does not guarantee improvements in brain function. Constant Therapy provides tools for self-help and tools for patients to work with their clinicians

comments: Problems for people with dimentia or Alzheimers... It is NOT appropriate to ask them how well they are remembering things, understanding things, etc.as this app does with the user. Do not do that! It's embarrasing and very upsetting to people with those conditions to be asked those questions. If someone is using it with them, that person can answer those questions for them if it can be done without their hearing or seeing the questions. It is a good idea for someoneto do the exercises with them.

Went thru the baseline activities. Then was asked if I wanted to subscribe. Since I had no info on what subscription would entitle me to, plus no idea how much it would cost, I chose subscribe. But the page wouldn't load. Waited about 3 mins then X'd out of the app. I believe the app could help me, but I'm most likely out of the game because I'm on a very tight fixed income (disability).

great idea. not edited properly. I have went through multiple questions and there are multiple correct answers, however if you do not guess the CT APP correct answer your answer is deamed wrong. Even simple ones where you have to identify the symbols. There were 5 symbols, but it only lets you mark 4 of them. Good idea, poor follow through. Or you have to say the name of the picture, the picture is of a persons legs at a beach. If you say beach it us wrong because they are looking for LEG.

I have been looking for an app like this for a few years. Paid $2000 out of pocket to get all my strengths and weakness after multiple TBI's. After you register, you find out, you can only use it for15 days, then have to get a note from a doctor to use it, and pay them. I don' t mind paying for an app to help me. Getting a doctor note, when you are on a fixed income, w/o insurance is what I object to. If I ready needed a doctor I get a nice cash only based rate, but this is not neccessary.

Was excited to find something to improve my cognitive abilities, then I read the "about game" and found the app is free for 15 days, then you have to pay $25 a month, or $250 a year, or $350 for 2 years!!! I have been out of work since having a stroke (4 months). I can't afford $25 a month when I'm struggling to pay my electric bill, have already terminated the TV, phone is next to cut. App is free only for therapists and those working in the medical field. DON'T INSTALL. WASTE OF TIME.

title: Gaming for stroke rehabilitation
description:
PhysUp: Gaming for stroke rehabilitation is a game developed to train the skills that can be affected after suffering a Cardiovascular Accident. With a simple gameplay, the user will work:

- Attention and processing speed
- Learning and memory
- Communication and language skills
- Visual and spatial information (distinguish figures and environments)
- Planning and decisions (objectives and plans)

The player will move through mazes. At first, the game gives you a keyword for a few moments, and the player must remember it and move through the maze to find the figure that is associated with that word.

PhysUp offers fun exercises to increase adherence to treatment. This is a complement to rehabilitation therapy and in no case a substitute

title: TOP WAYS TO AVOID STROKE
description:
Stroke prevention can start today. Protect yourself and avoid stroke, regardless of your age or family history.
What can you do to prevent stroke? Age makes us more susceptible to having a stroke, as does having a mother, father, or other close relative who has had a stroke.

You can't reverse the years or change your family history, but there are many other stroke risk factors that you can control—provided that you're aware of them. "Knowledge is power," says Dr. Natalia Rost, associate professor of neurology at Harvard Medical School and associate director of the Acute Stroke Service at Massachusetts General Hospital. "If you know that a particular risk factor is sabotaging your health and predisposing you to a higher risk of stroke, you can take steps to alleviate the effects of that risk."

How to prevent stroke
Here are seven ways to start reining in your risks today to avoid stroke, before a stroke has the chance to strike.

title: Stroke App:Hub
description: Stroke App:Hub is a mobile application which rapidly connects Stroke Doctor to Emergency Department. Stroke protocol is initiated from emergency department using TiaTele Cart mobile application and enables providers to assess and monitor stroke patients. The solution includes internet audio and video call, secure text and customizable rules with capability to broadcast messages and group calls. Physician scheduler is integrated for the 1st on call and 2nd on call doctors Vascular and Interventional Neurology doctors. Hardware devices includes Telemedicine cart with IP camera, iMac and various wireless medical equipments. The stroke workflow guides the physicians through NIH Stroke Scale assessment and stroke protocol chart as guidelines for diagnosing and making treatment decisions. Patient status with time tracking from ‘Last Known Well’ and ‘Door-​to-​Needle Time’ is shown for analyzing the stroke protocol execution efficiency.

description:
Welcome to Neofect Connect!

Neofect Connect offers the best mobile rehabilitation solutions for people recovering from a stroke.

Neofect has studied stroke rehab strategies for years. We have combined extensive medical research with cutting-edge technology, to produce a uniquely effective mobile rehab program. Based on the information you share with us,  you will receive customized daily rehab contents directly from our skilled therapists. Your program will enable you to set and achieve real world goals by participating in daily exercises and skills training activities. Neofect Connect also offers valuable daily readings and educational material relating to stroke rehab, mental health, lifestyle, and more. Start your morning with Neofect Connect! Neofect Connect: we connect you to rehab, we connect you to health, and we connect you to support. We aim to be your partner. We aim to inspire hope.

title: Visual Field Test Anxiety APP - Glaucoma/Stroke
description:
For very long time, nervous system injuries and diseases were thought to be irreversible, although neuroplasticity (ability of cells to change continuously throughout an individual's life )  was discovered in 1923 by American scientists Karl Leshley.

Currently, it has been confirmed that nerve cells continue to regenerate throughout life, not just until adulthood is achieved.

The following is an abstract from scientist Bernhard A Sabel 2017 study     https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Bernhard_Sabel

https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/27504612
 

In summary, visual training stimulates restoration of affected areas and electrical stimulation does so in a shorter amount of time.
 

About this program

This program provides visual training of the retina, optic nerve and visual cortex through the range of visual algorithms. What has been proven is that visual exercises subjectively and objectively affect visual functions. The question remains, what kind of visual stimulation algorithms work the best?

The initial purpose of this program was to help myself and to add another potential tool to slow down the progress of my own glaucoma. As of November 2019, it has been 20 years since my initial diagnosis and I am doing well. The glaucoma specialist who treated me all these years deserves my deepest gratitude.


How to use this program

Look at the center fixation point but take notice of each flash on the screen. Some flashes are completely random and others are somewhat predictable through the use of different geometric algorithms. In some ways, the training is similar to an actual visual field test experience, but there is no anxiety or pressure that is usually present.

I recommend practicing twice daily, no longer than 20 minutes at a time. During each session, practice 5 to 6 options, 3 to 5 minutes each. Select different background colours, object sizes and intervals. Switch between larger and smaller object sizes and intervals. Practice with each eye separately but also with both eyes.
 
Immediately stop if your eyes become tired. Do not practice longer than 20 min in one session.

I recommend listening to music while watching the flashes.  It will be less boring and it would involve other important brain areas. Many studies have established that there is a enhancing link between visual and auditory cortex performance.

Note: Program can be used on the desktop if one of Android emulators is downloaded.

Most importantly is to regularly visit your eye specialist and follow their advice, take your drops as prescribed, exercise and follow healthy eating directions. 

*Disclaimer:  It is important to emphasize this program does not replace the help of a glaucoma specialist and does not claim to cure or slow the progression of glaucoma.

Good luck!

title: STROKE-ER Rapid Evaluation Tool
description:
Currently, most ERs have a myriad of conflicting 'pathways' and guidelines and 'teams' and 'protocols', but it all comes down to the moment when you as the treating physician is standing in front of the patient trying to make a simple YES or NO decision. 

NOTHING IS IGNORED OR GLOSSED OVER

And to make that YES or No decision, the most important thing is to be able to consider all of the data that MUST be considered before making the decision. And no one can dispute that the amount of data that must be processed and taken into consideration before making a decision is fairly extensive. Inevitably,
when the ER is busy, much of this gets overlooked or glossed over or simply not looked at. 

FAST, TRANSPARENT AND THOROUGH

The objective of STROKE-ER is simple. It enables you to enter all the pertinent data that is required to make a balanced decision, 
without overlooking anything. Data input is fast and intuitive and you can do it all on your android phone. The app then processes this data and gives you a summary that you can review to make sure that the data is accurate and gives you a chance to fill in anything you have overlooked. Then you hit ANALYSIS and the algorithm processes your data and presents you with clear suggestions. 
The whole thing should take around 10 minutes. In addition to processing patient eligibility for IV TPA during the 4.5 hr window, 
STROKE-ER also processes eligibility for endovascular treatment under the 6-hour window and also processes eligibility under DEFUSE3 and DAWN criteria.

LEGALESE

Stroke ER is not an EMR, and does not accept or store or relay any identifiable patient information.

Please note that this is an educational aid, and STROKE-ER does not claim to diagnose or treat any disease or condition and claims no accuracy and has not been validated in any studies. Medicine is an ever-changing science. We do NOT warrant that the information in this app is accurate or complete and we are not responsible for any errors or omissions or for the results obtained from the use of the aforesaid information. Like any other tool, it works best in the hands of those already well versed in the field.


WE LISTEN TO YOU

Feel free to download and test it out. We are open to any suggestions for improvement, please email us at service@neurology.us.com.

Currently, most ERs have a myriad of conflicting 'pathways' and guidelines and 'teams' and 'protocols', but it all comes down to the moment when you as the treating physician is standing in front of the patient trying to make a simple YES or NO decision.

NOTHING IS IGNORED OR GLOSSED OVER

And to make that YES or No decision, the most important thing is to be able to consider all of the data that MUST be considered before making the decision. And no one can dispute that the amount of data that must be processed and taken into consideration before making a decision is fairly extensive. Inevitably,
when the ER is busy, much of this gets overlooked or glossed over or simply not looked at.

FAST, TRANSPARENT AND THOROUGH

The objective of STROKE-ER is simple. It enables you to enter all the pertinent data that is required to make a balanced decision,
without overlooking anything. Data input is fast and intuitive and you can do it all on your android phone. The app then processes this data and gives you a summary that you can review to make sure that the data is accurate and gives you a chance to fill in anything you have overlooked. Then you hit ANALYSIS and the algorithm processes your data and presents you with clear suggestions.
The whole thing should take around 10 minutes. In addition to processing patient eligibility for IV TPA during the 4.5 hr window,
STROKE-ER also processes eligibility for endovascular treatment under the 6-hour window and also processes eligibility under DEFUSE3 and DAWN criteria.

LEGALESE

Stroke ER is not an EMR, and does not accept or store or relay any identifiable patient information.

Please note that this is an educational aid, and STROKE-ER does not claim to diagnose or treat any disease or condition and claims no accuracy and has not been validated in any studies. Medicine is an ever-changing science. We do NOT warrant that the information in this app is accurate or complete and we are not responsible for any errors or omissions or for the results obtained from the use of the aforesaid information. Like any other tool, it works best in the hands of those already well versed in the field.


WE LISTEN TO YOU

Feel free to download and test it out. We are open to any suggestions for improvement, please email us at service@neurology.us.com.
summary: aims to end the chaos that surrounds stroke management in the ER.

title: ibis Paint
description:
ibis Paint is a popular and versatile drawing app downloaded more than 100 million times in total as a series, over 2500 materials, over 800 fonts, which provides 379 brushes, 71 filters, 46 screentones, 27 blending modes, recording drawing processes, stroke stabilization feature, various ruler features such as Radial Line rulers or Symmetry rulers, and clipping mask features.

*Youtube channel
Many tutorial videos on ibis Paint are uploaded to our YouTube channel.
Subscribe it!
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCo2EevPr79_Ux66GACESAkQ

*Concept/Features
- A Highly functional and professional features surpassing that of desktop drawing apps.
- Smooth and comfortable drawing experience realized by OpenGL technology.
- Recording your drawing process as a video.
- SNS feature where you can learn drawing techniques from other users' drawing process videos.

*Features
ibis Paint has high functionality as a drawing app along with features of sharing drawing processes with other users.

[Brush Features]
- Smooth drawing at up to 60 fps.
- 379 kinds of brushes including dip pens, felt tip pens, digital pens, air brushes, fan brushes, flat brushes, pencils, oil brushes, charcoal brushes, crayons and stamps.
- Various brush parameters such as starting/ending thickness, starting/ending opacity, and initial/final brush angle. 
- Quick sliders that allow you to quickly adjust brush thickness and opacity.
- Real time brush previews.

[Layer Features]
- You can add layers as many as you need with no limit.
- Layer parameters that can be set to each layers individually such as layer opacity, alpha blending, adding, subtracting, and multiplying.

*In-app purchases
ibis Paint provides you with the “Prime Membership” (monthly payment) , which enables you to use fully fledged functions. The more people become a prime members, the faster we can develop our application. We would like to create more functions, so please consider becoming a prime member.

[Prime Membership]
A prime member can use the prime features. You can try it free for the one-month at the time of the first purchase.A prime member can use the following features and services
 - Prime Materials
 - Prime Fonts 
 - Tone Curve filter
 - Gradation Map filter
 - Clouds filter
 - Reordering artworks in My Gallery
 - No advertisements in screens except the Online Gallery
 *After you become a prime member with the 30 days free trial, if you do not cancel your “Prime Membership” at least 24 hours before the last day of the free trial, your “Prime Membership” will be automatically renewed and you will be charged for the automatic renewal.

*On Data Collection
- Only when you are using or going to use SonarPen, the app collects audio signal from microphone. The collected data is only used for communication with SonarPen, and is never saved nor sent to anywhere.

*Questions and support
Questions and bug reports in reviews will not be responded to, so please contact ibis Paint support.
https://ssl.ibis.ne.jp/en/support/Entry?svid=25

comments: Well, it's a just good app. But it might just be my tablet, but I ran into a problem no one else seemed to address. Whenever I have the app pulled up, the volume on my tablet is fine, but then when I exit the app or shut off my tablet while I am using the app then my volume is reduced to zero. It's usually not a problem, but when I'm say, listening to music? It goes completely mute whenever I have to import a picture or grab a reference. If this flaw could be fixed, that would be amazing.

It's a good app. Though there isnt rly any difference between this app and the free version. The prime membership in the free app is about £3, but i had to pay £8 for this and still have tp pay £3 to unlock filters and materials etc. The only difference rly is that it has more filters in it, like anime background and manga background and others, which i rarely use

Well I will be honest there's almost not difference between the free version and this one I mean yea there's no commercials on the top screen anymore and yea the tools you can customize them like you like and there free 24/7 but I was expecting more besides that I feel like I wasted money on it. It was my birthday money but whatever I still feel like I did I was expecting that I was gonna be able to edit my gallery but I thought wrong still the same thing Kinda sucks for me :(

I love it!. Maybe add a feature where you can bind drawing tablet keys :3 with ease! Also If its possible,I wish this was available on Windows and macOS by just downloading it straight from the website and be able to link google play account or apple account or even make a IbisPaintX account so we could transfer our data either from free version or paid version of this app which I paid for xp.like being able to link our accounts somehow to those who paid for this vers. and free vers etc.

I really like this app, but it's worth noting that its almost exactly the same as the free version! The only differences are that there are no ads and you dont have to watch hours of ads to unlock all the brushes. It has a lot of features, though perhaps not as many as procreate. Great app overall though 👍🏼

title: How to Prevent Stroke
description:
How to Prevent a Stroke, Studies have revealed that almost 80% of the families in US have a member who has suffered a stroke. One should make a few changes in habits and life-styles to avoid its occurrence.

High blood pressure is a factor which can cause stroke. One should administer medicines regularly if they already have hyper-tension and ensure periodical checks to maintain blood pressure within optimum levels. A monitoring machine for checking the pressure at home will be handy.

In this app more topics and related How to Prevent a Stroke will discuss:

- foods that prevent stroke
- 6 foods that prevent stroke
- foods to prevent stroke and heart attack
- how to prevent a stroke aspirin
- foods that cause stroke
- how to prevent a stroke from happening again
- how to stop a stroke in progress
- stroke prevention guidelines

Administering a blood thinner like baby aspirin of 81 mg will keep the blood flow at the optimum pace and prevent strokes. If the individual has a medical condition already, a stronger dose may be prescribed.

Managing high levels of stress and doing away with depression will improve the mental and psychological state and prevent occurrence of strokes. One should indulge in social activities, meditate, practice yoga, listen to music and reduce intake of caffeine and alcohol.

Smoking increases the risk of stroke. Passive smokers are also at a higher risk by 30%. One should quit smoking and curb the desire to smoke by indulging in walks after meals, chewing a gum, placing a tooth-pick in the mouth and so on. Help from a therapist can be taken for severe addicts.

High levels of LDL also increase the risk of strokes. One should have a diet low in bad cholesterol and rich in whole grain, vegetables, lean-meat, fish, and low fat dairy products. If the levels can not be controlled by diet alone, one should take medicines.

People with TIA run higher risks of stroke. They should seek medical help for preventing its occurrence.

Download How to Prevent a Stroke now for learn detail more.

title: Stroke counter PRO
description:
Stroke PRO APP
Allows to calculate the rating and drive/recovery ratio .
Calculated by 1 or 3 strokes, with or without ratio. Use the screen button or the hard button “volume”.
Help:
1. Example of calculation for 1 stroke. To calculate the rating press button “start/stop” – at the start of the 1st stroke and at the start of the 2nd stroke. To calculate rating and ratio press “start/stop” at the start of the drive and at the start of recovery. Thus, when you press the button for the last time, the position of the rower will be the same as when you pressed the button for the first time.
2. Information panel on top left (is handy if you want to use your previous settings):
а.  "1" or "3" – number of strokes
б. "R" is there if you calculate the rating and ratio.
в. "screen"  or "volume" – you are using the screen button or the hard button “volume”.
3. The panel on top right shows the number of times you have to press the button “stop/start” to calculate your selection (for 3 strokes + ratio – 7 times, for 1 stroke + ratio – 3 times, for 1 or 3 strokes without ratio – 2 times).
4. Under the rating and ratio value we is shown the time and percentage for drive and recovery. The time is taken as an average for 1 stroke, in SS.00.
5. To access menu use the button “menu” of your device.
6. The rating calculation method is in progress, suggestions are welcome.

title: Stroke Risk
description:
If blood supply to the brain is interrupted (because of blockage or  hemorrhage), brain cells begin to die within several minutes. This condition is called stroke. Stroke is a medical emergency. Stroke is the second leading cause of death worldwide. Some factors increase your risk of stroke. Many of them are modifiable. Therefore, stroke can be prevented if these risk factors are controlled. By answering the following questions we can calculate your relative risk of developing stroke, comparing with a person without these risk factors. And by preventing the risk factors or adopting the preventive factors, you can reduce the risk of developing stroke.

The app contains 3 pages. Page 1 is brief introduction. Page 2 ask about risk factors. Page 3 shows your relative risk of developing stroke.

The app is free of virus or malware. It contains no ad or in-app purchase.

title: Riscometro de AVC Pro
description:
Votado como primeiro lugar na categoria de APP para condições de saúde pelo "top doctors" (Inquérito HealthTap).

O App Riscometro de AVC foi classificado pela classe médica com a a nota 4.5 em 5.0  https://www.healthtap.com/apps/38635

Oito em cada dez AVCs são preveníveis - o seu é ?

O Riscometro de AVC é uma ferramenta única e de fácil uso para você obter seu risco individual de AVC. O Riscômetro de AVC é capaz de calcular o seu risco através da avaliação de uma série de fatores de risco tais como a idade, o sexo, a raça, o estilo de vida e outros aspectos de saúde que influenciam diretamente a sua chance de ter um AVC.  Foi  desenhado como uma nova arma para ajudar as pessoas e os profissionais de saúde a reduzir o risco e a incidência de AVC.

Voce pode participar de uma estudo internacional de pesquisa, o estudo RiBURST, onde ,  submetendo  seus dados para nós você vai nos ajudar a entender melhor o AVC, seus fatores de risco e desenvolver estratégias globais de prevenção. 

Aspectos:
- Endossado pela Federação Mundial de Neurologia, rsed by the World  Federation of Neurology e pela Associação Internacional de Neurologia e Epidemiologia.
- Salve e siga seus resultados.
- Envie seu resultados por e-mail a pessoas de sua escolha
- Acesso a videos de orientação de especialistas
- Aprenda sobre os quatro sinais-chave de AVC - S.A.M.U.
- Participe do estudo RiBURST

Para:
- Para as pessoas que querem cuidar da saúde, para indivíduos de alto-risco ou após AVC.
- Para idades de 20 a 90 anos.

Aprimore seu Riscometro de AVC para a versão PRO para orientações de condutas personalizadas, salve e siga resultados, opinião de especialistas, videos de orientação, envie por e-mail  seus resultados para pessoas da sua escolha. Compartilhe sua experiência através de rede sociais.

Fatos 

AVC é a segunda maior causa de morte em pessoas acima de 60 anos e a quinta maior causa de morte entre pessoas de 15 a 59 anos. Em adultos, AVC é uma das causas líderes em termos de dependência de longo prazo independente de sexo, raça ou local. 
Dezesseis milhões de pessoas tem um AVC por ano. Uma em cada seis pessoas terão um AVC e uma pessoa morre por AVC a cada seis segundos.

AVC pode ocorrer em qualquer idade e tempo.

Afirmação da Organização Mundial de AVC:
“ A grande vantagem do Riscometro de AVC é que ele permite a pessoa calcular seu próprio risco de AVC dentro dos próximos 5 a 10 anos. Armada com esta informação, o individuo com ajuda de seu médico pode reduzir o seu risco de AVC ou ataque cardiaco. É muito mais fácil prevenir um AVC do que tratar. Como disse um paciente meu: o melhor AVC é aquele que você nunca teve!” Prof. Stephen Davis, Presidente, Organização Mundial de AVC.


Sobre nós:
O Riscometro de AVC nasceu do cérebro do Professor Valery Feigin, no  AUT’s (Instituto Nacional para AVC e Neurociências Aplicadas) para reduzir a incidência de AVC e salvar vidas em todo o mundo. O aplicativo veio para o mercado através "AUT Enterprises Ltd" – escritório de transferência tecnológica na AUT – Universidade baseada na Nova Zelândia. O editor da versão brasileira do app é coordenada pelo Prof. Norberto Cabral, Universidade da Região de Joinville

title: FuglMeyer for Stroke - UE
description:
This app helps therapists in delivering the Fugl-Meyer assessment for the upper extremity (motor functions) to stroke survivors.
The app guides by instructing on the item to perform and allows to mark the performance of each item - the total score, and the four subsections, are shown at the end.
Speech guidance allows to proceed in the test without focusing on the device. It is recommended that therapists already are familiar with the Fugl Meyer assessment, about which full details can be found here:
http://www.neurophys.gu.se/digitalAssets/1328/1328946_fma-ue-english.pdf

Please review it and suggest improvements!

title: One-stroke
description:
Test the limits of your brain power!
One-Stroke is a game that most people have played at least once.
The rules are simple, but the game is deep. You have to use your head!
directional game,Simple puzzle game.

How to play One-Stroke:
Playing One-Stroke is very easy!
You have to pass through all the lines, but you can't go through the same line twice. 
We have a rich variety of stages!
Lines with arrows, that you have to pass through going a certain direction!
Lines with numbers, that you have to pass through in a certain turn.

Level Qualification Mode(Dan Mode):
Try to clear 5 randomly generated problems within 5 minute each.
If you can do this, you can level up! 
It's a mode that you can play over and over, whenever you have time.

Completely free:
If you are completely stumped, there are also hints and answer guides available.
Of course, everything is completely free.

At present, there are 100 problems. You can play until 2nd Dan level. 
If you want more, we will continue to add new ones!

title: Stars Line - One Stroke Puzzle Game
description:
In this free-to-play puzzle game, your mission is to connect the stars with one line to solve puzzles and collect zodiac elements.

In this game, I tried to take the classic 'one line' puzzle, where a player has to connect a group of dots with only one continuous line, and I put it into a starry theme, where you have to connect a group of stars using one stroke to solve a puzzle.

The game has twelve levels/constellations. To move to the next one you need to solve the constellation's puzzles and open the zodiac element associated with it. So can you beat the game and collect all the zodiac elements?

The game features:
*Clean, intuitive and beautiful UI, and UX.
*Free game.
*No ads and no IAP.
*For the current version, the game has +100 puzzles.
*More puzzles are coming with the soon updates.

title: RP3 Rowing
description:
RP3 Rowing is a free application designed for the RP3 Rowing Ergo meter to run on newer Android devices. Once connected, it provides an advanced training tool that any rower or paddler can use to get real-time stroke rate, speed, distance, heart rate and other data.   

The big advantage is the real time Force Curve, which gives you a detailed feedback over your rowing stroke. Every stroke of every workout is recorded and saved for later review. Additional it can upload your workouts to the RP3 
Rowing Online Logbook (in a future version). You can build your own workout scheme based on 
time, distance, strokes and heart rate.

Furthermore the data can be adjusted for boat type and weight to get the right 
output, which can be compared with the boat you are rowing. This data is 
accurate within 0,5% to the times on water.  

With every stroke you have a choice out of 20 different data features to display. 
Just tap a tile and you will get a list of all the possible data, select the data you 
want and it will be displayed. In this way you can build your own screen.

The workout setting is easily done by adding the different training goals you like 
to go for. Set a number and hit the ‘+’ button and it will be added in the workout 
scheme. When you start rowing the programmed workout will be shown in the 
top of the screen and a pacer and a countdown will tell you how much to do. 

Enjoy all future upgrades.

* Displays your rowing data in real time.
* Offers a choice of following data:
  - Stroke number
  - Power per stroke
  - Average power per stroke
  - Stroke rate
  - Time
  - Stroke length
  - Distance
  - Distance / stroke
  - Est. 500m time
  - Energy / stroke
  - Energy sum
  - Pulse
  - Work per pulse
  - Peak force
  - Peak force position
  - Peak force position relative to stroke length
  - Drive time
  - Recover time
  - Stroke time
  - Drive : recover ratio
  - Boat speed
  - K value (resistance factor)
*Logs all your rowing workouts, including intervals, splits and heart rate information.
*Uploads workouts directly to the RP3 Rowing Online Logbook (in a future version)
*Displays weight-adjusted scores.
*Allow you to view different units on your monitor and device (for example, you can display watts on the device while viewing average pace on the monitor).

Requirements:
*RP3 Rower (from model RP3 - 2010)
*Eken 7” tablet standard on RP3S from august 2014
*Android RP3 cable (available from RP3 Rowing), part number 14001 for €10,00.
*USB Cable and a USB OTG (On-The_Go) Adapter (available from Amazon, Monoprice and other online vendors). RP3 part number 14002 for € 12,95
*A compatible Android device with a firmware version that supports USB Host mode. To test compatibility, use the "USB Host Diagnostics" to pass all tests, then RP3 Rowing for Android will work.

Android versions 4+ support USB Host mode.

Please note that RP3 Rowing cannot guarantee compatibility with any particular device. Manufactures frequently make changes that may disable RP3 Rowing, or you may have an earlier version than we tested. Some devices may require additional steps or special hardware to make it work, and some will never work.

title: ABC of Stroke
description:
This Wiley source of information, ABC of Stroke, is developed by MedHand Mobile Libraries. Improve your performance with relevant, valid material which is accessed quickly and with minimal effort in the palm of your hand using MedHand’s patented technology.

Stroke is the most common cause of adult disability and is of increasing importance within ageing populations.

This brand new title in the ABC series covers the entire patient journey, from prevention through to long-term support. It includes primary prevention and management of risk factors for stroke and secondary prevention including pharmaceutical, lifestyle and surgical intervention. The general principles of stroke rehabilitation are also addressed as well as mobility, communication and psychological problems, as is stroke in younger people. It also covers long-term support for stroke survivors and their carers.

This is an invaluable and practical guide to all aspects of stroke for both health care professionals and lay audiences. It is of particular relevance to general practitioners, junior doctors, nurses and therapists working with stroke patients and their carers, and to people with stroke and their families.

Editors:  Jonathan Mant, Marion F. Walker
________________________________________ 

MedHand Mobile Libraries offers a SUBSCRIPTION FREE application without edition upgrade. MedHand is the exclusive partner of Oxford University Press, publishing the latest editions of their Medical Handbooks series.

MedHand applications improve your performance with relevant, valid material that is accessed quickly at the point of care! 

Offering the most trusted and well recognized medical guidelines provided by excellent publishers such as McGraw-Hill, RPS, PDR Network LLC, Wiley-Blackwell and more.

title: Riskometar za moždani udar pro
description:
Stroke Riskometer Lite voted #1 Medical Conditions app category by top doctors (HealthTap survey).

The doctor's rated the Stroke Riskometer app 4.5/5 - https://www.healthtap.com/apps/38635

Eight out of 10 strokes are preventable – is yours?

The Stroke Riskometer PRO is a unique and easy to use tool for measuring, monitoring and managing your individual stroke related risk. The Stroke Riskometer is able to calculate your risk through evaluating a series of risk factors such as age, gender, ethnicity, lifestyle and other health factors that directly influence your likelihood of a stroke, and provide personalised management advice. It has been designed as a new weapon to help individuals and health professionals reduce the risk and incidence of stroke.

You can also elect to join an international research study, RiBURST, where you can submit your data to help us better understand stroke, its risk factors and develop global prevention strategies. 

Features:
-	Endorsed by the World Stroke Organization, the world’s leading organization in the fight against stroke, the World Federation of Neurology and the International Association of Neurology and Epidemiology.
-	Quickly assess your risk of stroke over the next 5 to 10 years.
-	Assess quarterly, half yearly or yearly to monitor your risk of stroke. 
-	Save and track your results.
-	Email results to the person of your choice.
-	Experts’ advice videos.
-	Learn about four key signs of stroke – F.A.S.T.
-	Join RiBURST study
-	
For:
-	Individuals who want to manage their health, at-risk individuals and for post-stroke individuals.
-	For ages 20 to 90+ years old.

Upgrade to Stroke Riskometer PRO for personalized management advice, save and track results, view experts’ advice videos, email your results to the person of your choice

Facts

Stroke is the second leading cause of death of people over 60 and the fifth leading cause of death in people aged 15 - 59. In adults, stroke is one of the leading cause of long-term disability irrespective of sex, ethnicity or location. 
Sixteen million people a year experience a stroke. One in six people experience a stroke in their lifetime and someone dies of a stroke every six seconds.

Stroke can occur at any age and at any time.

Endorsement:
“The great advantage of the Stroke Riskometer is that it allows a person to calculate their risk of stroke within the next 5-10 years. Armed with this information, an individual can take action, with the help of their doctor, to reduce their risk of having a stroke or a heart attack. Stroke is much easier to prevent than treat. As one of my patients stated, the best stroke is the stroke you never had!” Prof. Stephen Davis, President, World Stroke Organization.

About us:
Stroke Riskometer is the brainchild of Professor Valery Feigin, from AUT’s National Institute for Stroke and Applied Neurosciences, to reduce the incidences of stroke and save lives all over the world. It was brought to market by AUT Enterprises Ltd – the technology transfer office of AUT – a University based in New Zealand.

The Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) series from Focus Medica are extremely useful reference sources designed to enhance the understanding and dispel misconceptions regarding common diseases and disorders. title: Pakistan Stroke Registry
description:
Pakistan stroke registry is a national registry for stroke patients. This study will enroll patients with diagnosis of stroke (ischemic and hemorrhagic).

Purpose of this study is to identify risk factors, stroke types / sub types, presentation, care and outcome of these patients.

Patients will be enrolled from more than 70 centers throughout country including AJ Kashmir. Target enrollment is 5000 per year over three years (2019-2022)

 

This study is endorsed by Pakistan Stroke society

 

This study is supported by:

Health RAB, Pakistan

 

Ethical clearance of this study is approved by:

 Ethics review committee, Aga Khan University

National Bioethics commission, Pakistan

title: How to Prevent Stroke
description:
This application is useful for those of you who want to prevent stroke
How to prevent stroke

A stroke occurs when part of the brain doesn’t get enough blood. When this occurs the cells don’t get oxygen or nutrients and they die. The best way to prevent a stroke is to live a healthy lifestyle and manage any other medical conditions you might have that may increase your risks. If you or someone you are with may be experiencing a stroke, call emergency responders immediately.

Part 1
Reducing your Risk with a Healthy Lifestyle

*Eat a healthy diet*
A healthy diet will help you reduce your risks of obesity, high cholesterol, high blood pressure, and diabetes. Each of those conditions raises your risk of having a stroke. To lower the risks of developing these conditions you can:
Reduce your salt intake. This will lower your risk of developing high blood pressure. You can reduce your salt consumption by not sprinkling table salt onto your food, not salting pasta or rice water, and purchasing canned foods that say low sodium. Check the ingredients in processed foods. Many have a high salt content.
Eat a low fat diet. A fatty diet increases your risk of clogged arteries. You can easily eat less fat by choosing lean meats like poultry and fish and trimming the fat off of red meats. Drink low fat milk or skim milk instead of whole milk. Eat eggs sparingly because they are high in cholesterol. Check foods labeled “diet” or low fat- they can surprise you with sodium and fat content!
Control your caloric intake. Eating a high calorie diet places you at a higher risk for diabetes and obesity unless you are extremely physically active. Limit your intake of highly sugary foods like candies, cookies, and pastries. The processed sugar provides calories without the nutrients that will make you feel full. This can make you prone to overeating.
Increase the fruits, vegetables, and whole-grains that you eat. These foods are generally low fat and high in nutrients. They will supply you with the energy that you need without excess fat and calories.

*Exercise*
Exercise an excellent way to reduce your risks for strokes, diabetes, heart disease and obesity. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and the National Stroke Association make the following recommendations:
150 minutes per week of moderate physical activity. Moderate physical activity includes things like power walking, biking, or doing water aerobics. This should be in addition to two days per week of weight training.
75 minutes per week of intense physical activity. These activities cause you to work harder than the moderate activities. Examples include jogging, sprinting, swimming laps, and biking up hill. This should also be paired with weight training twice per week.
Do three 10 minute periods of exercise per day if you do not have the time for more. This may include walking to work, walking during your lunch break, and walking home from work. The exercise doesn’t have to be done all at the same time. Bring a friend with you to make it more enjoyable.

Thank you for using our application.
Don't forget to check out our other applications.
Hopefully this is useful for you.

title: Heat Stroke
description: Heat stroke, also known as sun stroke, is a type of severe heat illness that results in a body temperature greater than 40.0 °C (104.0 °F) and confusion. Other symptoms include red, dry or damp skin, headache, and dizziness. Onset can be sudden or gradual. Complications may include seizures, rhabdomyolysis, or kidney failure. Heat stroke occurs because of high external temperatures or physical exertion. Risk factors include heat waves, high humidity, certain drugs such as diuretics, beta blockers, or alcohol, heart disease, and skin disorders. Cases not associated with physical exertion typically occur in those at the extremes of age or with long term health problems. Diagnosis is based on symptoms. It is a type of hyperthermia. It is distinct from a fever, where there is a physiological increase in the temperature set point.

title: Stroke Scale
description:
The stroke (CVA) is the most common cause of deaths in Brazil and usually leaves sequelae in most survivors. Therefore early recognition and appropriate treatment are essential. Hypertension and atrial fibrillation are two major risk factors. The ischemic stroke may be 80% and 20% hemorrhage.
The NIH Stroke Scale (NIHSS) is a systematic use tool that allows a quantitative assessment of neurological deficits associated with stroke. This scale was originally designed as a research tool to measure the initial neurological status in clinical trials of acute stroke. Currently, the scale is used in acute stroke therapy and as a guide in predicting the prognosis.
The NIHSS can then be used as an evaluation tool to document the clinical neurological status in patients with acute stroke. This scale is valid for predicting lesion size and severity of stroke. The NIHSS has shown prognostic value in both the short and long term, in stroke patients. Additionally, the scale used to monitor the patient's condition, useful in planning care, and allows a common language for information exchange among health professionals. The NIHSS was designed to be a simple, valid and reliable, which can be applied at the bedside consistently by physicians, nurses or therapists.
descriptionHTML:
The stroke (CVA) is the most common cause of deaths in Brazil and usually leaves sequelae in most survivors. Therefore early recognition and appropriate treatment are essential. Hypertension and atrial fibrillation are two major risk factors. The ischemic stroke may be 80% and 20% hemorrhage.
The NIH Stroke Scale (NIHSS) is a systematic use tool that allows a quantitative assessment of neurological deficits associated with stroke. This scale was originally designed as a research tool to measure the initial neurological status in clinical trials of acute stroke. Currently, the scale is used in acute stroke therapy and as a guide in predicting the prognosis.
The NIHSS can then be used as an evaluation tool to document the clinical neurological status in patients with acute stroke. This scale is valid for predicting lesion size and severity of stroke. The NIHSS has shown prognostic value in both the short and long term, in stroke patients. Additionally, the scale used to monitor the patient's condition, useful in planning care, and allows a common language for information exchange among health professionals. The NIHSS was designed to be a simple, valid and reliable, which can be applied at the bedside consistently by physicians, nurses or therapists.

title: DrCardio+ D
description: The app provides evidence based estimate of Heart attack/ Brain stroke risk (cardiovascular event risk) in next 10 years. The app is developed for the WHO epidemiological sub-region D consisting of countries Algeria, Angola, Benin, Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Cape Verde, Chad, Comoros, Equatorial Guinea, Gabon, Gambia, Ghana, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Liberia, Madagascar, Mali, Mauritania, Mauritius, Niger, Nigeria, Sao Tome And Principe, Senegal, Seychelles, Sierra Leone, Togo. The app underestimates the risk to some extent. It is a app for health action on the part of user. Please go through the privacy policy and documentation for understanding the implications of risk. The people are often not aware of the risk of catastrophic cardiac events and are found unprepared when such an event strikes. The doctors are usually not aware of the existence of tools to identify the risk. Others use European risk predictors as they are available online. The app informs both about the risk of fatal as well as non fatal event combined as one combined risk estimate. The app also has links to assess the risk status online for those interested in knowing the combine risk of death due to heart attack which is also known as ischemic heart disease, coronary artery disease, CAD, CHD, coronary heart disease and also stroke which occurs due to blockade of the arteries of the brain (ischemic stroke) or the rupture of the arteries of the brain which results in a hemorrhagic stroke. The young people are less at risk compared to old people as age is a significant risk factor for development of heart attack or stroke which can result in disability and death. These conditions are very bad for the individuals suffering from stroke or heart attack also known as myocardial infarction.  These diseases are important because heart attack can lead to a variety of complications like heart failure organ failure,  erectile dysfunction dementia inability to walk pulmonary edema dilated cardiomyopathy. The sufferers of stroke also have a bad complications profile. They can develop mental derangement, speech abnormality, loss of limb function due to paralysis, loss of vision impairment of hearing impotence urinary and fecal incontinence. The app helps young people determine their risk even without spending money in an economical manner even without conducting medical tests. People can download the app and get as much information as they can get by scheduling an appointment with a trained general practitioner, cardiologist or endocrinologist. The app can help the doctors give documented proof of evidence based medicine that can be verified by the patient at their own level. The higher risk is synonymous with higher disability, higher mortality and even at time other social problems also occur. There have been cases when the disability due to paralysis or heart failure has resulted in loss of job and domestic issues like violence, divorce, promiscuity, prostitution have cropped up due to the potential risk of loss of income.  The app is for medical students, health workers, naturopaths, homeopaths, and doctors like anesthetist surgeons specialists to identify the patient with higher risk and refer the patient to cardiologist for expert consult. Mauritius has high prevalence of diabetes , hypertension and kidney disease. These disease also add to the risk subtended by being diabetic status high hba1c hypertension and smoking. The systolic blood pressure is a better marker of risk and the Mauritius has high number of hypertension patients. Mauritius also have very high number of diabetics . Increasing age of population a mixed population and very expensive life puts a special stress on an average Mauritian resulting in a high prevalence of risk factors. we sincerely hope use of this app gives a very good help to people wishing to know about their health status

title: Advanced Language Therapy Lite
description:
Take your aphasia therapy to the next level with four evidence-based advanced apps that build on the skills established the best-selling Language Therapy 4-in-1 app. This free sample of the new value-priced advanced app lets you try four popular speech therapy apps to help you improve. 

YOU'LL GET TO TRY THESE 4 APPS:

-----

1) ADVANCED COMPREHENSION THERAPY
Practice understanding sentences with three activities to improve listening and reading skills. 

-------

2) ADVANCED NAMING THERAPY
Practice word-finding skills with four activities to improve verbal expression.

-------

3) ADVANCED READING THERAPY
Practice reading at the paragraph-level with three levels of difficulty with comprehension questions and audio support.

-------

4) ADVANCED WRITING THERAPY
Practice typing at the word, sentence, and paragraph levels along with strengthening sound-letter relationships.

-----

WHO IS THIS APP FOR?

*Stroke survivors with mild or moderate aphasia (impaired language)
*Brain injury survivors with high-level cognitive-communication impairments
*Speech-language pathologists (SLPs) who work with adult communication

TRY FOR FREE!

Download Advanced Language Therapy Lite to try each of the four apps for free. Then purchase all four in Advanced Language Therapy, or purchase only the ones you need separately. 


THE TACTUS THERAPY DIFFERENCE

In all Tactus Therapy apps for speech therapy, you'll get wifi-free use, no log-ins, and no subscriptions. The activities are based on researched techniques that work. The content is designed with adults in mind, yet can easily be used with older children and teens. Support is built-in to encourage independent use for home practice while being flexible for in-clinic use with a qualified clinician.

Looking for something different in a speech therapy app? We offer a wide range to choose from. Find the right one for you at tactustherapy.com/find

title: Nutrition Stroke
description:
The Nutrition Stroke helps the patients to self-manage Stroke trough nutrition, using interactive tools. This app gives the patient important information regarding the most common doubts about nutrition for patients with this condition in an understandable way. This app also allows the patient to know how many calories should be eating in order to maintain the weight. Another amazing functionality of this app is a food dairy where the patient can record the food eaten. The patient can then show these records to the doctor and together improve the patient’s quality of life.

Besides, the user can test its knowledge regarding Stroke and nutrition in an amusing way through a little and fun quiz. 

Some information provided may not be valid for residents of other countries due to variations in medical practice and drug approval and indications.

This patient education application provides patients and Health Care Practitioners with easy to access information on Stroke management.

Reserved only for BBD’s Partners.

title: Stroke Value Golf
description:
Zacznij grać lepiej w golfa !

Program Stroke Value określa słabe i mocne elementy w Twojej grze w golfa i podpowiada odpowiednie treningi celem poprawy gry. Tee shot, długa gra, pitching, chipping, gra z bunkra, putting - dowiesz się które elementy są na odpowiednim poziomie dla Twojego handicapu, a nad którymi musisz popracować i jak to zrobić. Program podpowie jakie rodzaje i typy treningów należy stosować, aby Twoja gra w golfa była skuteczniejsza, a Twój handicap niższy.

Stosując regularnie program Stroke Value systematycznie poprawiasz swój poziom gry w golfa, wiesz co i jak ćwiczyć. Gra staje się przyjemniejsza i zaczynasz częściej wygrywać w turniejach.
Masz też możliwość porównania skuteczności swoich różnych swoich uderzeń z innymi graczami w tym z graczami PGA Tour.
Opisy i schematy treningów zalecanych dla danych uderzeń są bardzo dokładne i dostosowane do określonego poziomu graczy. Dotyczą one 10 typów uderzeń tj. Tee shotu, Długiej gry, Długiego pitchingu, Krótkiego pitchingu, Chippingu, Gry z bunkrów fairwayowych i bunkrów przy greenie, Długiego, Średniego i Krótkiego puttingu.
Program może być zarówno przez amatorów jak i graczy zawodowych.
Autorem programu jest Krzysztof Czupryna oraz firmy Target54 i GolfHelp.

Stroke Value to program, który zmieni Twoją grę w golfa !
