title: Table Tennis Strokes
description:
Unveil the secrets of pro players, learn and practice with Table Tennis Strokes app and become a better table tennis player today!
This invaluable and unique table tennis learning tool is designed to fit the needs of every table tennis player who wants to improve the playing technique. The focus of the app is on the stroke definitions explained through detailed key body parts positions and movements. It tackles the most important aspects of the table tennis game revealing the secrets of the professional players.
It’s simple and easy to use with intuitive user interface and great features such as:

Pro-player demonstration
The strokes demonstrations are done by a professional table tennis player and recorded with a hi-speed camera.

30 strokes description
The 30 most important strokes in the table tennis game are covered in the app divided into 3 categories: Forehand, Backhand and Serve&Receive.

3-phase strokes explanation
To make it easier to understand and implement the learned skills each stroke is divided into 3 stroke phases: 
Phase 1: Preparation - before the player hits the ball, 
Phase 2: Hit - the moment of the racket-ball contact, 
Phase 3: Finish - the follow-through after hitting the ball. 

Interactive body key-points Images
Focusing on the players body parts such as hands, shoulders, feet, knees, wrists,  ankles, head, eyes etc., Table Tennis Strokes indicates the most important points on the human body with a very simple and easy to implement instructions and advices that suggest the best body parts positions for the most effective strokes and game play. This method brings a fast learning curve so users can expect to perform correct and efficient strokes in a very short time with ease and discover the new dimension of the table tennis sport and enjoy the game.  

Video loop
Table Tennis Strokes has 30 video loops recorded in a real-life table tennis environment performed by a professional table tennis player.

Slow-motion frame control
The app has a very useful tool for analyzing the players in slow-motion. It enables users to carefully study each fraction of a second (frame-by-frame) by dragging a slider button and playing the video in slow-motion both backward and forward.

Download Table Tennis Strokes to discover and learn the secrets of this magical sport.

title: CHA2DS2-VASc HAS-BLED Score Calculator
description:
CHA2DS2-VASc Calculator - Calculates stroke risk for patients with atrial fibrillation afib. Although this risk level self-assessment is not intended to replace the essential risk assessment you need with your healthcare provider, it can help you visualize the risks for stroke you may be facing. 

HAS-BLED is a scoring system developed to assess 1-year risk of major bleeding in patients taking anticoagulants with atrial fibrillation.

The higher your levels, the higher you are at risk.

title: KMCH STROKE UNIT
description:
A Health Care Provider of Western Approach with an Indian Touch.

KMCH is the most trusted Multispecialty Hospital in the Southern Indian City of Coimbatore.

The relentless service of KMCH in the past 26 years, taken health care to the most modern levels in the region catering to urban and rural population.

KMCH Mobile Stroke Unit 
TREATING STROKE AT THE DOORSTEP
Stroke is amongst the biggest killer in the modern times. Even if the patient survives, it can destroy the quality of life. A ‘Clot Buster’ drug can save your life if you get it inside 3hours of having a stroke. But the drug can be administered only after a CT Scan. To ensure patients in Coimbatore region get access to the drug and CT scan as fast as possible, KMCH has launched the Mobile Stroke Unit. It provides a means to quicker and better stroke care when it’s needed most. Designed as a specialized emergency room on wheels, the Mobile Stroke Unit is staffed 24/7 with a critical care nurse, paramedic and CT technologist. It is equipped with a CT scanner that can immediately determine the type of stroke a patient is experiencing and how to treat it. The Mobile Stroke Unit includes lab testing equipment and clot-busting drugs that can greatly save the life of stroke patient. The Mobile Stroke Unit can reduce the time it takes to diagnose and treat patients for stroke, thus greatly improving survival and recovery of the patient.

title: SmartLine - One stroke drawing
description:
Once upon a time, everybody have had played it once: The one stroke drawing. So let recall our childhood again with a new challenge and fun game.

Game play is very easy:
  Pass through all lines in just only one drawing stroke 
  Do not pass through a line twice

SmartLine is a puzzle game, with a concept of 3S:
  Simple
  Smart
  Smile

title: Bet & Stroke Tracker
description:
BS Golf stands for Bet & Stroke Tracker, this app will help you have perfect control of your bets and strokes you give or receive with your playing buddies.

It doesn’t matter if you bet for $1 usd or for thousands I’m sure you keep a note in your phone or a notebook in your bag to keep track of how many strokes of advantage should be applied the next time you play, and if you are extremely organized you keep track of the amount of money you win or lose thorough the year and you keep in your mind your best round and the average you shoot.

With BS Golf Tracker you will be able to have this full control and stats with just a few clicks.

Add the players, add the bets you play and just enter the final result, if you don’t play with someone for a long time you can go to the player profile and see the exact detail of the last round you guys played together.

You can also add group bets to the round so you can keep the exact amount of your balance without having to add it player by player.

title: Calligraphy Lettering Arts
description:
For our first tutorial in "Mastering Calligraphy", we're going to start with an easy alphabet that uses the two basic strokes we learned in the easy introduction. Just those two strokes make up a majority of the letters in the Roundhand Script alphabet. We'll be breaking the letters into similar groups and mastering both the lowercase and uppercase letters. 

Calligraphy adds creative flair to handwritten projects and, even more than being beautiful – which it definitely is, calligraphy is an analog skill that offers much needed respite in our digital world.When teacher taught her calligraphy classes at CreativeLive, she shared some essential tips and techniques all beginner calligraphers can use to improve their letter forms and calligraphy style.

When brush lettering, make sure your downstrokes are all consistently angled. Use more pressure. The downstrokes are the thick parts of brush lettering. Making your own calligraphy guide can help with the angle a ton. You won't always need to use the calligraphy guide, but practicing with one while you're learning can help you develop the muscle memory needed to create consistent and beautiful letters in the future.

When those skills are separate in your head and (more importantly) in your hand, you’ve mastered the basics of how to write calligraphy. That’s the essential simplicity of it.(If you're wondering how to write calligraphy with different sorts of tools such as felt-pens, square brushes etc, you might like the 'Five Options' calligraphy tutorial.If you're looking for a quick-and-easy calligraphic effect or you've hit a wall in your calligraphy practice, you might want to have a look at the page on 'easy' calligraphy.)

1. Calligraphy is not as fluid as classic cursive. Each letter you write should be an individual character, so don’t try to connect them fluidly like you would, say, your signature. Try to write one cursive letter, and then pick up your pen. Start the next letter by “connecting” it to the letter before it. Practice makes perfect.
2. After you’ve written and connected your letters, go back with your writing utensil and “darken” your downstrokes. So sketch over your word again, and anywhere your pen would’ve moved downward, thicken the line. Your upward strokes should remain thin.

title: Advanced Naming Therapy
description:
Take your speech therapy to the next level! Practice word-finding skills for adults with aphasia after stroke with this evidence-based app.  Four engaging activities give you lots to talk about in new ways as you improve higher-level expressive language skills including thought organization, attention to detail, and mental flexibility.

 **Try Advanced Naming in Advanced Language Therapy Lite for FREE**

Advanced Naming Therapy is your next step up from our best-selling Naming Therapy app - perfect for the speech therapy clinic and home practice for people with aphasia, cognitive-communication challenges, and unclear speech after stroke. Challenging, fun, and perfect for groups, Advanced Naming Therapy will be your “go-to” app for verbal expression.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

4 Trusted Activities:

1) CREATE sentences using 250 action words based on the evidence-supported Verb Network Strengthening Treatment (VNeST) method for aphasia. 
2) GENERATE words in over 300 sound- and meaning-based categories to stretch your mental dictionary as you improve verbal fluency and speed after stroke. 
3) DESCRIBE over 500 interesting photographs that will make you laugh or scratch your head – and talk!
4) COMPARE and contrast over 200 pairs of items from concrete to abstract using verbal reasoning skills.

Over 1,250 unique stimuli – you won’t get bored as you improve with this exciting speech therapy app!

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Here’s what you’ll be able to work on:

    • Word Finding
    • Sentence Creation
    • Verb Conjugation
    • Semantic Organization
    • Non-Literal Language
    • Verbal Reasoning
    • Synonyms
    • Mental Flexibility
    • Speed of Processing

These activities can help people with aphasia or anomia after stroke, cognitive-communication challenges after brain injury, tip-of-the-tongue sensation during conversation, or other cognitive and communication challenges.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Helpful features and settings:

    • Track progress easily with automated reports that include data and responses
    • Assess verbal fluency easily with built-in tests with published norms
    • Record your voice with on-screen audio recording you can email
    • Adaptable to any level with multiple input methods: type, dictate, or choose
    • Learn quickly with helpful instructional overlays that guide you

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Download now to get started – or try it for FREE with Advanced Language Therapy Lite!

Looking for something different in a speech therapy app? We offer a wide range to choose from. Get the right one for you at https://tactustherapy.com/find

title: Jellow Plus
description:
Jellow Plus AAC app is an aid for the speech & communication therapy. It usages picture, text and voice.It helps in improving the speech and communication disabilities among children with Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Down’s syndrome and in adults  with speech disabilities like Stroke & Aphasia thereby empowering them.They can use Jellow Plus to 
express their thoughts, needs and wants, to get access to education and thus social inclusion.

This application is organized into three levels - Basic, Intermediate and Advanced. In the basic level the user can communicate by using 6 icons with 12 predefined expressive sentences which cater to the immediate needs of the patient (like Stroke & Aphasia patients) while staying in hospital.The intermediate level provides 18 icons with 36 predefined expressive sentences that can use by patient (like Stroke & Aphasia patients) during their recovery at home.Moreover, this application allows single touch communication which makes it easier to bridge the communication gap between the patient and their caregiver, as the patient can convey their needs efficiently.

The advanced level has more than 3000 icons with grammar categories like Nouns, Verbs, Adjectives, Adverbs, etc. to build sentences.This level will help the user in communication due to its vast vocabulary.

Jellow Plus is developed at the IDC School of Design at the Indian Institute of Technology Bombay (IIT-Bombay) located in Mumbai.If you have any suggestions for us to improve the application, please submit your feedback/comments via email or our web site - www.jellow.org at jellowcommunicator@gmail.com

This application is available in the name of "Jellow Plus".

title: Stroke Care
description:
Stroke Care is designed specifically for patients recovering from a stroke, their families. It helps to explain strokes, range of motion exercise, and available activities of daily living. The app, created by a team of stroke specialists, provides easy-to-understand information on strokes, exercise and activities of daily living. 


 Stroke Care is designed specifically for patients recovering from a stroke, their families. It helps to explain strokes, range of motion exercise, and available activities of daily living. The app, created by a team of stroke specialists, provides easy-to-understand information on strokes, exercise and activities of daily living. 

Key Features
- Designed specifically for patients and the non-medical community

- Stroke disease information (Classification of stroke / Early symptoms of stroke / Prevention and clinical symptoms of stroke)

- ROM exercise information

- 6 categories of ADL (mobility, walking, dressing, caring for body parts, eating/drinking, and toileting) video and guideline

- Provide Male and Female version

- Provide Rt. hemiparesis and Lt. hemiparesis version

- Provide Korean subtitle and English subtitle

If any exercises are too difficult and cause pain or increase stiffness in your limbs, do not do them.

title: FAST Test
description:
Suspect a stroke? Think FAST!
 
The main aim of the FAST campaign is to help people recognise the symptoms of a stroke - and to think FAST.
 
With over 18,000 people in Scotland having a stroke every year, it is essential that people can recognise a stroke when it's happening and take prompt action by dialling 999. 
 
The app teaches you how to recognise the signs of stroke including video clips and when to dial 999. You will also find information on stroke and links to our websites. You can also use the app to call our Freephone CHSS Advice Line Nurses for confidential advice and information.
 
Find out more at www.thinkfast.org.uk

recentChanges:
Version 0.1.4 includes a significant visual improvements: strokes are no longer "cut off" where they intersect. This change makes characters look much cleaner but also improves learning, since the old graphics gave away information about the next stroke to write. This version also includes many character and word list fixes.

NOTE: The new stroke graphics require downloading the character data again, which may take a few minutes.
comments: A nice, simple app that has a lot of potential. Right now the stroke recognition needs a *lot* of work, though. Sometimes a non-ubiquitous stroke order is enforced. Other times it will misidentify a stroke and (through newfound leniency?) mark some random future stroke. Other times it will flash at me telling me to make a stroke that literally has already been marked. The multi-click process for correcting the auto-grading that is often incorrect after running this gauntlet rounds out an unfortunately frustrating user experience.

A well made and useful app that I use daily to retain 汉字 in memory. There are glitches though. Some stroke orders are wrong, e.g. 再 (wrt to Pleco) and certain strokes are not recognized well, like 月 in 期. I would also prefer the ability to edit lists in the app, rather than continuously importing external lists as I learn new charaters.
an excellent (and open-source!) alternative to Skritter

Excellent app for learning 汉字, and much better than Skritter in terms of usability and pricing. I've been using the free download from GitHub for a long time, and was only glad to pay for the Play Store version.
Very good alternative to Skritter

title: NIHSS StrokeJuice
description:
NIHSS StrokeJuice (pro version) is a medical application designed and coded by physicians for physicians to record, save, archive, review, and email NIH Stroke Scale scores (abbreviated neurological assessment). The application can track the following times associated with important stroke alert (aka brain attack) events: hospital operator pages/calls to neurologist, patient arrival at hospital, physician at bedside of patient, NIHSS stroke score, and CT scan. Save and access data for multiple patients. Simple and fast NIHSS entry interface.


This is the standard or "pro" version of the application, which does not have ads on the main page (unlike the lite/diet version). 

At this time not intended for any clinical applications.

title: Asia Pacific Stroke Conference (APSC) 2018
description:
About Asia Pacific Stroke Organisation (APSO)
Fifteen million people suffer from stroke worldwide each year. In the Asian region alone, nine million people suffer from a stroke. The burden of stroke presents as a massive challenge not only in the Asian region but on a global scale.

To face the challenges of stroke disorders in the Asia Pacific region, the executive committees of the Asia Pacific Stroke Association and the Japan Stroke Forum made a formal decision to merge, resulting in the establishment of the ‘Asia Pacific Stroke Organisation’ (APSO). One of the principal aims of APSO is to unite as a strong, connected body to fight the menace of stroke in the Asia Pacific region. APSO is a registered, charitable business in Hong Kong and an affiliate of the World Stroke Organisation. The executive committee of APSO is strongly committed to the cause of alleviating stroke and play a fundamental role in raising the standard of stroke care in Asia, particularly in countries with limited resourcing and training.

title: PRESS calc
description:
PRESS (Predictive Swallowing Score) is a prediction tool applicable to people who suffered an ischemic stroke leading to dysphagia and impairment of oral intake. Given some clinical characteristics, it provides estimates of the probability to recover functional oral intake within a user-defined time period (up to 40 days). 
PRESS can provide time-dependent predictions for dysphagia recovery after stroke. It might help guide clinical decisions in dysphagic stroke patients involving the placement of feeding tubes (nasogastric tube feeding or percutaneous endoscopic gastrostomy feeding).

PRESS should only be used in people
• who have suffered ischemic stroke AND
• who have impaired oral intake

PRESS should NOT be used in people with 
• pre-existent dysphagia OR
• recurrent stroke within the prediction time-frame OR
• late hospital admission > 48 hours after stroke onset.

title: HP Telestroke
description:
Stroke has emerged as a second biggest killer of mankind world over and even in India more people die of stroke than infectious diseases like tuberculosis. Age adjusted stroke prevalence in India ranges from 84 to 424 per 100,000 according to various studies and annual incidence ranges from 105–262/100,000. There is no data available from H.P. but it is estimated from national statistics that H.P. should have 15,000 to 20,000 patients of stroke and  every year 5000–10,000 new patients suffer stroke. This number is bound to increase with increased life expectancy and aging of population. After a stroke about 50% patients do not survive beyond 6 months and 25% become dependent for life. So not only mortality but morbidity due to stroke is also overwhelming.
Stroke is of two kinds: one due to rupture of brain blood vessels called hemorrhagic stroke and other is caused by blockage in brain vessels called ischemic stroke. A CT-scan of head can reliably differentiate between the two. Ischemic stroke is much more common and amounts to up to 80% of all strokes. The common symptoms of stroke are sudden appearance of: deviation of face, weakness or numbness of limbs, difficulty in speaking, unsteadiness, giddiness and headache.  The simplest way to treat ischemic stroke would be to remove the blockage in brain vessels and now the drugs are available which can dissolve the clot blocking blood vessels. However this drug which is an injection called recombinant tissue plasminogen activator(tPA) can be given within 4.5hrs of onset of stroke symptoms. Therefore it is most important that people recognize stroke symptoms at the earliest and rush to hospital with CT-Scan facility and availability of this drug.
Himachal Pradesh is a small hilly state in the Northern part of India. Covering an area of 55,673 kilometres (34,594 mi), it is a mountainous state.  It has a population of 6,856,509 with population density of 123/km2, 90% of which lives in villages as per the provisional results of the Census of India 2011. It has 12 districts with population ranging from 32,000 to 1.5 crore. It has two tertiary care hospitals with four neurologists, two in each hospital. So given the difficult terrain and just four neurologists, delivering stroke treatment seemed like a distant dream.
However in March 2014 under the guidance of Stroke Specialist Prof. M.V. Padma from All India Institute of Medical Sciences, New Delhi and on the initiative of Additional Chief Secretary Health to Govt. of H.P., Sh. Vineet chaudhary  a Telestroke Project was envisaged. All the government hospitals with CT-Scan facility were roped in.  Out of 17 such hospitals, eight and nine centers respectively were attached to each of the two tertiary care centers. Workshops were conducted at various district hospitals. Medical officers in these hospitals (M.B.B.S. graduates and internal Medicine postgraduates) were trained in recognizing stroke through these workshops.  They were taught reading plain CT-scan head to rule out hemorrhage even without the help of radiologist and written protocols for thrombolysis in ischemic stroke with explicit inclusion and exclusion criteria were provided. Blood sugar and ECG were only other investigations to be done apart from CT- head before thrombolysis. Tissue plasminogen activator was made available at all these centres and provided free of cost through hospital pharmacies. All the four neurologists were made available on phone 24x7 and whenever any ischemic stroke came in window period they were to be contacted. It was decided to use social networking sites like “Whatsapp for transmitting CT-scan images to neurologists for consultation. These hospitals were than designated as primary stroke centres. Without any extra infrastructure requirement or any new manpower the project was finally launched in May-June 2014 amid much skepticism about its success.
The app empowers general public with Stroke Awareness and related action in emergency

Padma from All India Institute of Medical Sciences, New Delhi and on the initiative of Additional Chief Secretary Health to Govt. of H.P., Sh. Vineet chaudhary a Telestroke Project was envisaged. All the government hospitals with CT-Scan facility were roped in. Out of 17 such hospitals, eight and nine centers respectively were attached to each of the two tertiary care centers. Workshops were conducted at various district hospitals. Medical officers in these hospitals (M.B.B.S. graduates and internal Medicine postgraduates) were trained in recognizing stroke through these workshops. They were taught reading plain CT-scan head to rule out hemorrhage even without the help of radiologist and written protocols for thrombolysis in ischemic stroke with explicit inclusion and exclusion criteria were provided. Blood sugar and ECG were only other investigations to be done apart from CT- head before thrombolysis. Tissue plasminogen activator was made available at all these centres and provided free of cost through hospital pharmacies. All the four neurologists were made available on phone 24x7 and whenever any ischemic stroke came in window period they were to be contacted. It was decided to use social networking sites like “Whatsapp for transmitting CT-scan images to neurologists for consultation. These hospitals were than designated as primary stroke centres. Without any extra infrastructure requirement or any new manpower the project was finally launched in May-June 2014 amid much skepticism about its success.
The app empowers general public with Stroke Awareness and related action in emergency

title: Heat Stroke
description: Heat stroke, also known as sun stroke, is a severe heat illness, defined as hyperthermia with a body temperature greater than 40.6 °C (105.1 °F) because of environmental heat exposure with lack of thermoregulation. This is distinct from a fever, where there is a physiological increase in the temperature set point of the body. The term "stroke" in "heat stroke" is a misnomer in that it does not involve a blockage or hemorrhage of blood flow to the brain. Preventive measures include drinking plenty of cool liquids and avoiding excessive heat and humidity, especially in unventilated spaces, such as parked cars, that can overheat quickly. Treatment requires rapid physical cooling of the body.

title: 뇌졸중 STOP
description:
아직도 나는 뇌졸중과 상관이 없다고 생각하십니까?

-> 당신은 술을 좋아하고, 금연에 실패를 하며, 과체중으로 고민하시나요?
 그렇다면 앞으로 뇌졸중 환자가 될 가능성이 있습니다.

-> 당신의 가족들은 혈압, 당뇨, 비만, 흡연, 과음, 심장질환으로부터 자유로우신가요? 만약 이들 중 한 가지라도 해당이 된다면 앞으로 뇌졸중이 될 가능성이 있습니다.

하지만 걱정하실 필요는 없습니다.
앞으로 뇌졸중 Stop! 어플리케이션과 함께 꾸준히 관리하면서 뇌졸중의 위험에서 벗어날 수 있도록 뇌졸중 Stop!이 도와 드리겠습니다.

★ 이 어플리케이션의 특징

나는 물론이고 내 가족 중 누구라도 대신 관리해줄 수 있다.
뇌졸중 퀴즈를 풀면서 나도 모르게 뇌졸중 예방과 관리에 박사가 된다.
뇌졸중 발병 위험요소를 내 스스로 관리하면서 꼭! 필요한 정보를 얻을 수 있다.
뇌졸중 치료에 중요한 약물 복용 시 복용시간을 알려주는 알람기능이 있다.
와파린(쿠마린) 복용 시 약물의 효과에 방해가 되는 비타민 K 가 많이 들어있는 식품의 정보를 얻을 수 있다.

★ 메뉴 소개

1. 나의 정보
- 이 어플리케이션을 사용 할 사람의 정보를 입력합니다. 
  나 이외의 가족을 등록할 수 있습니다.
- 내가 주로 사용하는 뇌졸중 위험인자 중 3가지를 저장하여 보다 쉽게 사    용 할 수 있습니다.

2. 뇌졸중 바로알기
- 뇌졸중에 대한 기초정보로 뇌졸중이란, 뇌졸중의 종류, 위험인자(고혈압,     당뇨병,고지혈증,흡연,음주,비만,심방세동),경고증상,응급처치,뇌졸중          의 치료에 관한 내용으로 뇌졸중에 대해서 꼭 알아야할 필수 정보로        구성되어 있습니다.

3.뇌졸중 퀴즈
- 뇌졸중에 관한 간단한 지식을 확인할 수 있으며, 향후 지속적으로 새로운    퀴즈의 업데이트로 뇌졸중에 대해 좀 더 자세한 정보를 얻을 수 있습니다.

4. 뇌졸중 관리수첩
- 혈압 : ① 측정된 혈압을 입력하여 나의 혈압을 주 단위나 월 단위 평균              혈압과 그래프로 혈압의 변화를 알 수 있습니다.
         ② 자가혈압측정시 주의사항을 알고 올바른 혈압을 측정 할 수 있              도록 돕습니다. 
         ③ 우리가 많이 사용하는 양념의 소금함량표가 있어 지나치게 짜
            게 먹는 식습관으로 혈압을 올리지 않도록 도와줍니다.
         ④ 소금을 적게 먹는 실천방법을 알려 줍니다 
         ⑤ 한국인이 외식 시 주요 섭취 식품의 나트륨 함량을 알려줍니다.

- 혈당 : ① 측정된 혈당을 입력하여 나의 혈당을 주 단위나 월 단위 평균              혈당과 그래프로 혈당의 변화를 알 수 있습니다.
         ② 당과 당뇨병에 관한 정보를 제공합니다.
         ③ 저혈당이 생겼을 시 대처요령을 알려줍니다.


- 비만 : ① 비만도를 측정해서 알려줍니다.
         ② 운동하는 방법을 알려줍니다.
         ③ 체중을 감소하는 5가지 원칙을 알려줍니다.
         ④ 건강한 식생활을 위한 5가지 원칙을 알려줍니다.         
         ⑤ 우리가 매일 접하는 식품성분표시법을 보는 방법을 알려줍니다.

- 금연 : ① 금연 할 때 금연일수와 절약된 비용을 구체적으로 알려줍니다.
         ② 금연 할 때 주변에게 알려서 지지를 받을 수 있습니다.
         ③ 금연 할 때 요령을 알려줍니다.
         ④ 금단 증상이 있을 때 대처법을 알려줍니다.         
  
- 음주 : ① 음주 할 때 음주일과 음주량을 기록하여 알 수 있습니다.
         ② 남녀의 음주 제한량을 알려줍니다.

- 검사기록: ① 병원에서 검사한 주요혈액검사의 경과를 기록할 수 있습니               다.

5. 약물복용관리
- 뇌졸중 치료에 중요한 약물의 복용시간을 알려주는 알람기능이 있습니다.
- 항혈전제에 관한 설명이 있습니다.
- 항혈전제 복용시 주의사항을 알려줍니다.
- 항응고제(와파린) 복용시 약효에 영향을 줄 수 있는 비타민 K 가 들어있    는 식품의 함량표를 제공하고 있습니다.

6. Information
- 뇌졸중 Stop! 어플리케이션의 사용 설명이 있습니다.
- 뇌졸중임상연구센터에 관한 설명이 있습니다.
- 뇌졸중Stop! 구체적인 기능에 대한 설명이 있습니다.
- 문의가 있을 경우 연락방법을 알려줍니다.

② 금연 할 때 주변에게 알려서 지지를 받을 수 있습니다.
③ 금연 할 때 요령을 알려줍니다.
④ 금단 증상이 있을 때 대처법을 알려줍니다.

- 음주 : ① 음주 할 때 음주일과 음주량을 기록하여 알 수 있습니다.
② 남녀의 음주 제한량을 알려줍니다.

title: SeLECT score
description:
Risk of late seizures

SeLECT predicts the absolute cumulative risk of late seizures after stroke. Late seizures are defined as spontaneous seizures occurring > 7 days after ischemic stroke. The 95% confidence interval for the risk estimates is given in brackets.

Prediction time

The user can choose a custom prediction time in months using the slider. The range is between 0 and 60 months.

Prediction graph

The prediction graph displays Kaplan Meier risk estimates for the calculated SeLECT value. X-axis is time in months, Y-axis is cumulative absolute risk in percent. The dotted line is the 95% confidence interval.

title: Cardiac Output & Volume Calculator: Cardiology
description:
"Cardiac Output & Volume Calculator: Cardiology" apps is designed to help health professionals, namely doctor, nurse, and paramedic, to calculate cardiac output, cardiac index, stroke volume, and stroke volume index. Cardiac output is the volume of blood pumped through your heart every minute. Stroke volume is the amount of blood pumped by your heart in every beat. The cardiac output in this apps is calculated with Fick equation.

Why should you choose "Cardiac Output & Volume Calculator: Cardiology"?
🔸 Best calculator to calculate cardiac output, cardiac index, stroke volume, and stroke volume index. 
🔸 A simple, accurate, and straightforward cardiac / heart calculator.
🔸 Interpretation and differential diagnosis based on the result of the calculation.
🔸 Cardiac output calculation based on the Fick equation.
🔸 It is totally free. Download now!

"Cardiac Output & Volume Calculator: Cardiology" apps will also give several differential diagnoses based on the result of cardiac output, cardiac index, stroke volume, and stroke volume index calculation. For example, a low cardiac output can be caused by hypovolemia, hypoperfusion, shock, arrhythmia, and severe metabolic acidosis. Calculations must be re-checked and should not be used alone to guide patient care. Download "Cardiac Output & Volume Calculator: Cardiology" app now!

For more info contact us at:
www.imedical-apps.com

title: Graffiti Pro for Android
description:
Download Graffiti™ - The Keyboard Replacement for Android that uses the stroke-based handwriting recognition system text input system made popular by Palm™ PDAs running PalmOS™.

Features:
-Replaces the Default Keyboard for Android
-Stroke-based text input - Uses the Graffiti™ alphabet text input method
-Easy to Learn
- Speeds up text input with Auto-Capitalization and Word Learning
-English and Japanese language support
-Faster and More Accurate that On-Screen Typing
-Advertisement Free 

Graffiti™ is a replacement for the built-in on-screen keyboard, also called an input method. With Graffiti, you no longer type but you draw Graffiti characters with your finger or a compatible stylus. Graffiti characters are mostly single-stroke drawings that closely match the usual alphabet, but are simplified to make entry faster and easier. For example, the letter "A" is entered with a stroke that looks like an upside-down "V", saving time that you do not need to cross the "A" in the middle. Same for the letter "T", which is entered almost like a "7".

There are text and numeric input areas, improving the recognition of your input. Strokes drawn in the text area will only be interpreted as letters; strokes in the numeric area will be interpreted as numbers .

If you were a user of a PalmOS based PDA in the past, this will all be very familiar to you as the input method used by those devices was a stylus drawing Graffiti strokes in an input area at the bottom of the display. But even if you were not a Graffiti user before, you should give it a try now if you find that the on-screen keyboard doesn't suit your input style.

Don't know the Graffiti alphabet? After installing and enabling Graffiti, just draw a stroke up from the Graffiti input area into the main display area and the help screen appears. Tap to switch between the six stroke help screens.

Watch the YouTube videos to get a sense of what this input system is like in action and read the comments and reviews.
Install video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=roTlELn8fE4
PocketNow video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sTQrnDpAO8U
CareAce video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3CbO7EpBhEY
Questions? Please see the FAQ at our website.

comments: Works just like Palm fast easy input I just used it to type this. If you never used a palm it will take a little practice. But I can write faster with Graffiti than I can type with my thumbs. If you swipe up on the example menu, it will show you all of the available key strokes!

Pretty good app. But there are a couple issues, for one, the little menu that shows you how to write all of the letters could be better. It doesnt show any gestures like spacing, deleting, writing commas, specal symbols, and i think it should be more like the actuall palm pilot one. Overall, pretty ok app.

Compared to regular Grafitti, the surface area of the writing area is much larger. I dont know whether it would be practical on a small phone. You would need to get the regular Grafitti. Grafitti is one of the great input inventions of tech. It's up there with the keyboard. It might be a little slower than gboard, but youll catch the errors faster. You can look at the words as you type, so you can correct them right away. You can look someone in the eye while you are taking notes. Fantastic.
Really good implementation and loved it the way I loved it the first time in my PDAs.

I like this text entry method because I learned it previously with Palm and preferred printing to a keyboard. Also it takes up less screen space than a keyboard. I wish the developers would keep it updated for newer operating systems.

title: BrainAttack
description:
BrainAttack App is an easy-to-use tool that helps doctors save the lives of stroke patients. The App helps doctors follow standard medical criteria to quickly determine patient eligibility for life-saving treatment known as tPA. The Brain Attack App offers a speedy & thorough process to determine tPA eligibility. Doctors can have confidence they are following standard of care guidelines.The App features tPA eligibility tool and NIH Stroke Scale.

-Criteria based on current practice parameters.
-Criteria established and tested by practicing Neurologists.
-Highly interactive tool using native Android touch features.
-App does not require internet connectivity.
-Provides real time feedback to user with color coded background based on responses to criteria.
-Ability to go back and forth to adjust user responses.
-Final summary result can be emailed.

The Stroke Scale is an implementation of the National Institutes of Health Stroke Scale (NIHSS). The NIHSS is a systematic assessment tool that provides a quantitative measure of stroke-related neurologic deficit.

-Native Android App based Stroke Scale that does not require internet connectivity to use.
-An easy to use interface that updates the Stroke Scale based on user responses to each Stroke Scale question.
-A Summary View of the user responses to all Stroke Scale questions and final Stroke Scale result.
-Ability to email the Stroke Scale results to yourself.

title: Pocoyo Pre-Writing Lines & Strokes for Kids
description:
With this application children will be able, through guided strokes in fun scenes featuring Pocoyó, to develop the necessary abilities and hone the fine motor functions needed to master writing-related movements, practicing the manual and visual skills involved.

The aim is to acquire the skills that they will later use to write.

The application contains 30 cards with which to learn and practice the proper movements, with curved and straight strokes, horizontal and vertical, oblique, and even some loop-like strokes and simple symbols.

Each card has a series of dotted lines that the child must trace with his finger, and indicating the direction in which to draw.

All the cards are set in the wonderful children's world of Pocoyó and his friends Nina, Pato, Elly and Loula, among others, with fun animations and effects that will act as positive reinforcements, encouraging children to practice and build their self-confidence as they progress.

Ideal for preschoolers and parents who want to see their children learn and have fun in a safe environment made just for them.

This application was created by teachers and professional designers of applications for children.

The application features parental controls in order to ensure a safe gaming and learning environment.

The application contains free cards so that you can try it out. 

If you like the application for your child, you can unlock all the tracing cards, and eliminate the advertisements with a single payment.

title: Number Therapy Lite
description:
Numbers communicate so much, yet they are often left out of communication therapy. Now stroke survivors can practice understanding, saying, and typing numbers at home to improve these essential life skills.

Age, dates, phone numbers, addresses, money, time, measurements, fractions, weight, years – numbers are everywhere and so important. Be more independent with communication with stronger number communication skills.

Would you be able to understand, write down, and tell someone this phone message?

“Your appointment is at 3:15 p.m. on August 3rd, 2015 at 1650 18th Avenue. Bring $5. Please call back to confirm at 785-5662.”

Work on all these number skills and more with the evidence-based Number Therapy app!

title: A Bold Stroke
description: Syed Imon Rizvi has proven that one can write powerful poetry by using simple nuances and vocabulary that even a child can understand and be motivated with. Because mainly the power of truth itself gives immense energy to a person to even share it further; and distribute it among masses. This book will touch the heart of each and every individual, who will read it with the understanding that it has been written under the influence of cries and sighs of the oppressed and poor. The greatest trait of poet's writing is that he expresses himself without feeling any pressure from worldly or materialistic influences. He puts everyone in the field of accountability; whether one is the president of the most powerful country on earth or the poorest person of the weakest country of the world.

title: ABCD2 Score
description:
The ABCD2 Score is a quick clinical tool that can help predict an early risk of stroke in the first 2, 7, and 90 days after transient ischemic attack (TIA).

The ABCD2 Score assesses the risk using five parameters:
Age
Blood pressure
Clinical features
Duration of TIA
Diabetes.

The main features of the application are:
-Getting the results with minimal screen touches
-Small application size
-Supporting devices with different screen size and orientation, including tablets
-English and Russian languages
-Manual language switching
-E-mailing a detailed test report
-No advertisement and banners
-No odds!
________________________________

Example of detailed test report:

Patient's ID: Smith J
Date & Time: 26/11/2012 22:05
Test: ABCD² Score

ANSWERS: 
Age: ≥60 years
Blood pressure: ≥140/90 mm Hg
Clinical features: Unilateral weakness
Duration: ≥60 minutes
Diabetes mellitus: Yes

RESULTS: 
Points: 7
Risk: High Stroke Risk
2-Day Risk: 8.1%
7-Day Risk: 11.7%
90-Day Risk: 17.8%
________________________________

Your feedback is very welcome. Please, use the feedback form in your application or e-mail it to cardioneurologyteam@gmail.com with “Android-ABCD2” in the subject line.

Please, help us to translate the application into your own language.

Keywords: ABCD2 score, stroke, neurology, transient ischemic attack, risk assessment, diagnosis, medical calculator

title: Advanced Reading Therapy
description:
If your reading skills have been impacted by a stroke or brain injury, this app can help you improve. Practice reading with engaging exercises that include text and audio supports.

** Try for FREE by downloading Advanced Language Therapy Lite **

Advanced Reading Therapy uses technology to assist struggling adult readers to make sense of paragraph- and multi-paragraph-level passages. Self-ratings encourage metacognitive awareness, comprehension questions test accuracy, and hints enable greater success and independence. Score reports make it easy to see progress (and write progress notes) along the three graded levels:

* Level 1: Shorter passages of 50 words or less, written around a Grade 0 – 1 reading level.  Three questions after each passage test comprehension.

** Level 2: Medium passages of 50-150 words, written around Grade 2 – 3 reading level. Four questions appear to see how well you understood.

*** Level 3: Harder passages get you ready for the texts you want to read. 150 – 600 words and Grade 3 – 6 reading level with five questions each. 

Adult readers will enjoy these functional and entertaining passages as they get back to reading the pages and screens in their own lives. Speech-language pathologists will love having so many modern reading passages with carefully-crafted questions at hand to teach strategies.

Built-in audio controls let you listen to a single word, go sentence-by-sentence, or hear the whole article – whatever you need. You’ll get over 200 reading rehabilitation exercises in 15 categories! 

Features:

• Text-to-speech available on touch
• Adjust font size, spacing, and rate at any time
• On-screen audio recording to listen to yourself reading aloud
• Self-rating of comprehension encourages metacognitive awareness
• Inference and prediction question encourage thinking outside the text
• Huge variety of topics to appeal to mature readers
• E-mail reports for easy data tracking
• Unique categories such as Jokes, Inferences, First Chapters, Text Messages, and Functional Passages
• Look back at the passage any time, or have the relevant text highlighted with a Hint 

Tactus Therapy offers a wide variety of apps to help with reading comprehension. Advanced Reading Therapy is the next step in your rehab after mastering the single words in Comprehension Therapy, the phrases and sentences of Reading Therapy, and the complex sentences of Advanced Comprehension Therapy. All of our apps work together to help you reach your reading goals. Find the right apps for you with our app finder: https://tactustherapy.com/find

title: TiaMD RapidResponzCPH
description: TiaMD RapidResponz is a mobile application which rapidly connects Stroke Doctor to Emergency Department. Stroke protocol is initiated from emergency department using TiaMD RapidCall mobile application and enables providers to assess and monitor stroke patients. The solution includes internet audio and video call, secure text and customizable rules with capability to broadcast messages and group calls. Physician scheduler is integrated for the 1st on call and 2nd on call doctors Vascular and Interventional Neurology doctors. Hardware devices includes Telemedicine cart with IP camera, iMac and various wrireless medical equipments. The stroke workflow guides the physicians through NIH Stroke Scale assessment and stroke protocol chart as guidelines for diagnosing and making treatment decisions. Patient status with time tracking from ‘Last Known Well’ and ‘Door-​to-​Needle Time’ is shown for analyzing the stroke protocol execution efficiency.

title: Tips to Prevent Heat Stroke
description:
Tips to Prevent Heat Stroke | Summer has finally arrived, bringing sun, heat, and plenty of ideas for outdoor activities. But don’t forget that exposure to heat can have negative consequences. Follow our advice to avoid heatstroke while enjoying everything that summer has to offer!

When we work under the hot weather, our body temperature rises and perspiration will cool our body down. However when perspiration cannot effectively play the role, we will suffer from dizziness, headache, nausea, shortness of breath and even unconsciousness; if the body temperature rises further to 41 degrees, it will lead to heat stroke which will be life-threatening.
 
In hot and humid environment, we should take appropriate measures no matter working at indoor or outdoor workplace (e.g., warehouses, docks, construction sites, container yards, kitchens and laundry rooms etc.). To avoid working in hot environment is certainly the best way to avoid heat stroke, but if not possible, download this app to check what measures should be adopted to prevent heat stroke.
